<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Helen" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Helen,</orth> 1) name of the wife of Menelaus: <bibl n="shak. son 53.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 53, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.153" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.5.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 5, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.146" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 146</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.146" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 146</bibl> and passim. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 44</bibl>. Mentioned, though not by name, in <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.244" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 244</bibl>. 2) the mother of the emperor Constantine: <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.142" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 142</bibl>. 3) female name in <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.208" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 208</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.144" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.137" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 137</bibl>. 251 etc. 4) female name in <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.202" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 202</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.71" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 71</bibl> etc. 5) in <bibl n="shak. cym 2.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 2, 1</bibl>. 6) confounded with <emph>Hero</emph> by Flute: <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 199</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>